com.interpss.core.net.childnet

Interface ChildNetInterfaceBranch

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChildNetInterfaceBranchImpl

    public interface ChildNetInterfaceBranch
extends org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject
    A representation of the model object 'Child Interface Branch'. Interface branch for defining parnet-child connection interface. It references to a parent network branch when it is defined. The branch could be moved to the child network when the parent network is splited into multiple networks.
    Interface branch is not used in the calculation. The interface bus pair is actually used in the calculation.

    The following features are supported:

    • Branch Id
    • Interface Bus Side
    • Child Net Side
    • Interface Bus Id Child Net
    • Container
    See Also:
    ChildNetworkPackage.getChildNetInterfaceBranch()
